    <briefdescription>
<para>An owning interpolation object that bundles a Lagrange builder and evaluator. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classLagrangeInterpolator" kindref="compound">LagrangeInterpolator</ref> constructs and owns a matching <ref refid="classIdentityInterpolationBuilder" kindref="compound">IdentityInterpolationBuilder</ref> and <ref refid="classLagrangeEvaluator" kindref="compound">LagrangeEvaluator</ref> for a given dimension. It satisfies the <ref refid="conceptconcepts_1_1Interpolation" kindref="compound">concepts::Interpolation</ref> concept and is the recommended way to create a Lagrange interpolation for use with advection operators and similar algorithms.</para>
<para>The builder is an identity operation: it passes function values on the interpolation grid directly as coefficients to the evaluator, which then performs local polynomial reconstruction via the Lagrange basis.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>ExecSpace</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The Kokkos execution space used for computations. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Basis</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The Lagrange basis type (uniform or non-uniform). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InterpGrid</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The discrete grid on which function values are provided. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>MinExtrapRule</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The ExtrapolationRule applied below the lower boundary. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>MaxExtrapRule</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The ExtrapolationRule applied above the upper boundary. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>DataType</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The floating-point type of the function values (default: double). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
